events.name: 話しかける並列・自動実行

parameters:
Sister Eleo: Have you understood the personality of the
priestess Sophia?

Mage Relm: A degenerate without any ambition to grow for two
years.

Thief Nora: She's someone who secretly sneaks out to the
neighboring town because her regular bar has disappeared...

Clea: When you lay out the facts, it's quite something,
isn't it?

Mage Relm: Well, this is what religious people are like!
They are people who don't have any doubts about musty
scriptures.
Thief Nora: E-Everyone! That's a bit too much to say...!

Sister Eleo: What do you understand about Sophia-san! She's
doing her best in her own way, you know!

Sister Eleo: Even the amount of alcohol she drinks has
decreased a little, just a tiny bit, since coming here.
She's making an effort!

Sister Eleo: And her efforts towards her healing techniques
are amazing! She was practically a novice, but she has grown
significantly in just a few years!

Sister Eleo: Even her clothing has improved! It used to be
much worse, but now it's better!\^

Sister Eleo: She's popular, mainly among men! She has
completely blended into this village now!\^

Sister Eleo: Certainly, she may be quite sloppy, but it's
not fair for everyone who hasn't even met her to say such
things!\^
Sister Eleo: I-I'm sorry... I got a little carried away.
Clea: No, it's okay. Should we go to the town of Camps?

Sister Eleo: If it's about Gara-san, there is credibility.
Everyone, please bring Sophia-san back with you.

Terios Church Cleric: Sister Eleo! The preparations for the
move are complete.
Sister Eleo: I'm going to Fort Roxos now.

Thief Nora: This is the hideout of the thieves' guild,
right!? A-Are you all going to be okay on your own?

Sister Eleo: It's also our job to reform lawbreakers like
them.
Sister Eleo: Then, let's meet later.

Thief Nora: It's a place where outlaws from the Camps region
gather. I haven't heard any good rumors about it. I'm
worried.

Mage Relm: There's no such thing as being completely
unprepared, right? Let's fulfill our own requests.

Clea: Yes, that's right... First, let's go to the town of
Camps.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Camps Region/The City of Camps
in the Grasslands\c[0]

Thief Nora: There doesn't seem to be anyone here. Are they
still in the Roxos Fortress?

Mage Relm: Such a precious time wasted... This is why I
dislike religious people.

Clea: Do the Terios Church and the Magic Academy have a bad
relationship?

Mage Relm: It seems that they used to be one organization,
but they split apart after conflicting with each other in
terms of faith and research.

Mage Relm: In my opinion, the role of a mage is to dispel
the fog of faith with intellect!

Clea: It seems you have returned, Eleo-san. Are you not
accompanying us?

Terios Church Priest: Huff...huff... It's terrible, Sister.
Eleo has been taken hostage!!

Clea: First, please calm down and let me hear what you have
to say.
Clea: Is Eleo-san kidnapped and they're demanding a ransom?

Terios Church Priest: We can't afford to pay such a large
sum of money, but if we don't do something, Sister Eleo will
be!

Mage Relm: Sigh, what should we do, Clea-san? I've been told
to follow your instructions, after all.
いますぐ助けにいきましょう

Terios Church Priest: Thank you very much! May the blessings
of the goddess Imiserinos be upon you.

Thief Nora: I know about the Roxos Fortress, so I'll guide
you there!
報酬をいただけますか？

Terios Church Priest: Understood... It's a small amount, but
please take this. Please take care of Sister Eleo.

Thief Nora: I know about the Roxos Fortress, so I'll guide
you there!

Mage Relm: You're quite the skilled negotiator... Let's
hurry up and go.

Sister Eleo: You're joking, right, Sophia-san? Saying that
you're leaving from here...

Priestess Sophia: I am serious. I truly appreciate all that
you have done for me.

Priestess Sophia: At that time, in front of the church,
you...

Sister Eleo: Please stop talking about memories!! I don't
want to hear such stories, why...

Priestess Sophia: Heroic deeds are considered to be the most
virtuous acts.

Priestess Sophia: As an act of atonement for my past sins, I
will go on a dragon subjugation with them.

Sister Eleo: That's... dragons... If you hate them and want
to leave here, just say it honestly!
Sister Eleo: I hate someone like Sophia-san!!

Priestess Sophia: Phew~ It seems like I'm the only one who
couldn't do it.

Priestess Sophia: The request is to persuade Eleo-chan and
join everyone on the journey to subjugate the dragons.
Clea: I appreciate your sentiment, but are you serious?

Priestess Sophia: Yes, of course. Even though I may not look
like it, I dislike jokes when I'm sober.
Clea: Understood, I will persuade Sister Eleo.

Priestess Sophia: Yes, please. Eleo-chan should be at the
orphanage.

Sister Eleo: I have understood the circumstances, and I will
allow them to accompany us.
Priestess Sophia: Thank you very much, Sister Eleo.

Sister Eleo: Please behave in a manner that does not bring
shame to the priestess of Irini Village.
Sister Eleo: Well then, take care.
Sister Eleo: You shouldn't just drink alcohol all the time.

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, while I can't completely abstain
from alcohol, I will make an effort to reduce it.

Sister Eleo: Please take care of your health and make sure
to rest properly even during the journey.
Priestess Sophia: Of course, there's no need to worry.
Sister Eleo: Ugh, why, all of a sudden... nooo!

Sister Eleo: S-Sophia-san!? Why all of a sudden... Did you
do something wrong?!

Sister Sophia: Oh my, it's truly sad that you have no trust
in me.

Clea: I'm here today on behalf of someone who wants to make
a donation, and Sophia-san has been helping me.

Sister Eleo: Indeed, we have received it. We will use it for
the repair of the church and the development of the village.

Sister Eleo: This is a gift that I believe all of you can
make good use of. Please use it to aid you in your
adventures.

Sister Eleo: With this, we should be fine with the
finances...

Sister Sophia: Oh my, are you still worried about Mr. Gara's
matter? It seems like there is a bigger issue than just a
financial problem.

Clea: Gara... Wasn't he the one whose bar burned down in a
fire?

Sister Eleo: Since the fire, Mr. Gara has been feeling down.
The nobles are strongly opposing the reconstruction of his
bar.

Sister Eleo: I will try to make a plea once again. Thank you
very much for your trouble, regardless of the outcome.

events.name: ソフィア（設置イベント）
テリオス教会僧侶・その後ソフィア

parameters: Terios Church Priest: Please, Sister Eleo.

Priestess Sophia: Eleo-chan should have gone to the
orphanage. I'll be waiting here.

Sister Eleo: I apologize for interrupting, but please don't
disturb us while I'm talking to Sophia-san.

Devoted Terios Follower: I used to be a merchant in the
past, but I had a change of heart. It's necessary in order
to be invited to the perfect world of Terios.

Returning Soldier: It's because the goddess Actina took away
three of my best friends in a battlefield I couldn't keep up
with.
Terios Church Priestess: Pray to the goddess Imiserinos.
Terios Church Cleric: Sophia, how is your journey going?

Terios Church Priest: A heroic act of slaying a dragon! I
respect you as both a follower of the Terios Church and as
an imperial citizen.
Terios Church Priest: May today be a good day.

Terios Church Priest: Alcohol in moderation, please! Eleo-
chan will start crying!

Terios Church Priest: Slaying dragons does not justify
excessive drinking!

Former prostitute woman: What is it? Do you have a complaint
about me?

Former prostitute woman: ...I used to be a prostitute, but I
ran away because I only knew how to sell my body, so I'm
worried about my future life.

Former prostitute woman: Thank you for listening. I'll
forget about my days as a prostitute and live together with
Imiserinos.

Former prostitute woman: It's never too late in life...
don't you think?
